Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine pink-beige. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) contains several such drawings Name Agelo(chos)? From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0035.23 and British Museum 1925,0119.330 and 2011,5003.255, 258 and 273.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0404)
